 as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["form of   John  , also used quite frequently in the English-speaking world. In Northern Ireland it is sometimes found as a variant of   Ewan ."]}]},{"name":"Atte","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Transferred use of the surname, which was derived in the medieval period from the Old English personal name <i>Tāta</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Joan Atte Gate was born about 1337, in England, United Kingdom as the daughter of Hamo Atte Gate. She married Robert Echyngham about 1367. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"ABT 1337–":"umbes 1337–Surnud","1337–Female":"1337–Surnud","1337–1413":"1337–1413","1365–Male":"1365–Surnud","1380–1464":"1380–1464","1374–1464":"1374–1464","1313–Male":"1313–Surnud","1337":"1337","1413":"1413","1313":"1313","1464":"1464","1365":"1365","ABT 1367":"umbes 1367","1374":"1374","ABT 1337":"umbes 1337","about 1374":"umbes 1374","1380":"1380",",,, England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Sussex, England":"Sussex, England"},"fi":{"ABT 1337–":"noin 1337–Kuollut","1337–Female":"1337–Kuollut","1337–1413":"1337–1413","1365–Male":"1365–Kuollut","1380–1464":"1380–1464","1374–1464":"1374–1464","1313–Male":"1313–Kuollut","1337":"1337","1413":"1413","1313":"1313","1464":"1464","1365":"1365","ABT 1367":"noin 1367","1374":"1374","ABT 1337":"noin 1337","about 1374":"noin 1374","1380":"1380",",,, England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Sussex, England":"Sussex, England"},"fr":{"ABT 133